{"title":"All the ways of styling React","description":"React itself doesn't come with any styling solution. So the community came with its own solutions. Here's a list of them.","date":"14 May, 2021","cover_image":"media/all-ways-style-react--cover.jpg","body":"<p><img src=\"\" alt=\"\" class=\"feature-image\" style=\"display: none;\"></p><div class=\"picture-container\">\n  <figure style=\"width: 100%;--padding-top: 66.66666666666666%;\">\n    <picture>\n      <source type=\"image/jpg\" media=\"(min-width: 501px)\" data-srcset=\"/assets//media/all-ways-style-react--cover/large.jpg\">\n      <source type=\"image/jpg\" media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" data-srcset=\"/assets//media/all-ways-style-react--cover/small.jpg\">\n      <img alt=\"Placeholder\" data-src=\"/assets//media/all-ways-style-react--cover/large.jpg\" class=\"lazyload blog-img\">\n    </picture>\n  </figure>\n  </div><p></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/photos/E-Zuyev2XWo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Johannes Plenio</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>React itself doesn't come with any styling solution out of the box. You can look at the docs, but you won't find a \"the-way\" to do styling. So the awesome community have come up with ways of styling, and boy, there are a lot of these. So I'm going to cover quite a lot of them in this article. Read on!</p>\n<p>So, we can</p>\n<h2 id=\"CSS-BEM\"><a class=\"heading-link\" href=\"./styling-react--all-the-ways#CSS-BEM\">#</a>CSS BEM</h2>\n<h2 id=\"CSS-Modules\"><a class=\"heading-link\" href=\"./styling-react--all-the-ways#CSS-Modules\">#</a>CSS Modules</h2>\n<h2 id=\"JSS\"><a class=\"heading-link\" href=\"./styling-react--all-the-ways#JSS\">#</a>JSS</h2>\n<h2 id=\"Styled-Components\"><a class=\"heading-link\" href=\"./styling-react--all-the-ways#Styled-Components\">#</a>Styled Components</h2>\n<h2 id=\"Emotion\"><a class=\"heading-link\" href=\"./styling-react--all-the-ways#Emotion\">#</a>Emotion</h2>\n<h2 id=\"styled-jsx\"><a class